args: Prepare for a magical, mystical,\nMARVELOUS circus unlike anything\nyou've ever seen before!
Forget your worldly cares and let us\nwelcome you to a world of dreams!
But first, I—Fritz the Magnificent—will\ndazzle you with my splendiferous\ndagger-throwing skills!
Those targets are miles away!\nIs he seriously gonna hit 'em?
He does seem to be throwing from a fair\ndistance further than normal.
No matter the target or the situation,\nI never miss what I set my eyes on.
Now watch as I hit yonder moving\ntargets...with my eyes closed!
No WAY he pulls this off!
SWEET CRISPY CARP! HE DID IT!
Next, I shall take requests from the\naudience on what targets to hit.
Please, do not be shy. Speak up!
You are SUCH a child sometimes.
I thank you most humbly for your requests.
I will now address them in order.\nFirst, we have...
Thank you all for attending our show today.\nWe look forward to having you again!
Hey, guys. Didn't know you were watching.
Yeah—and what a show it was!
I can't believe ya hit movin' targets what\nwith yer eyes shut. It blew my MIND!
Heh. That was nothing. You should—
That was the worst circus imaginable!
I've half a mind to demand compensation!
I am the daughter of a marquis, and yet\nwas forced to mingle in the same area as\nsome pack of slack-jawed plebeians!
A circus this shameless should go out of\nbusiness and make the world better for it!
Damn, SOMEONE woke up on the\nwrong side of the world this mornin'.\nWant me to tell her where to cram it?
I deeply apologize for the distress our\nhumble troupe caused you, madam.
Pfft! Are you that dagger-throwing buffoon?\nYou SHOULD be sorry!
What kind of circus doesn't know how to\ntreat nobility properly? A third-rate one,\nthat's what!
If I might be permitted an explanation,\nmy lady, there is a reason for our actions.
Oh, this had better be good.
To me, you are as a star that shines\nhigh in the evening sky.
The worlds we live in are so different that\nordinarily I would not even be permitted\nto gaze upon your beauty as I am now.
But when this once-in-a-lifetime chance\npresented itself, I knew I had to show you\nthe finest show from as close as possible!

Furthermore, as I felt myself to be
performing for you alone, I wished
to gaze upon your legendary beauty
as I did so.
As the box seats reserved for royalty are\nfar removed from the stage, my plan\nsimply would not have been possible.
What? Y-you were looking at me?
But...you couldn't possibly see me well\nfrom the stage...
For you see, your beauty burned more\nbrightly than even the lights which\nilluminate our grand stage.
Still, I cannot more deeply regret the\ndistress and unhappiness my selfish\nactions caused you.
If you had enjoyed our show as I wanted,\nI had hoped to one day perform in your\nmansion or other palatial abode.
But I see now that was never an honor a\nthird-rate performer like myself deserved.
Still, if I may ask one more favor before\nwe forever part ways, might I at least be\npermitted to see you off as an apology?
Before we forever part ways?! No, I...\nNo! You must not go!
In truth, I thought your show was simply\nwonderful! I was just, uh, too proud to\nadmit I enjoyed it so much.
I would LOVE to have you come perform\nfor me!
If that is your wish, my lovely lady,\nthen I shall see it done.
You will not regret your decision!\nI will take you to a world beyond\nyour wildest imaginings!
By the time I am finished, you won't want\nto return to the real world.
Wow. He's REALLY good at this.
If he butters her up any more,\nthey can sell her as popcorn.
Ha! Score one more performance for us!\n...Hmm? What's up, you two?
I'd rather keel over than say that kinda\nstuff to some rich snob!
Ha! But you heard me at the start of\nthe show, right?
No matter the target or the situation,\nI never miss what I set my eyes on.
That goes for the audience's hearts,\nas well.
Anyway, I'd better go tell the others\nthe good news.
See you back at the castle,\n{player_name}!
He really meant what he said at the\nbeginning.
